:: Testing for Tori's variables system

:*
 * Things to make that involve variables:
 * X Variable definitions
 * - Variable lookups (using variables in equations / other variables)
 * X Changing (or setting) variable values outside of definitions
 *
 * Errors involving variables:
 * X Improper operators
 * X Invalid types
 * X Extra identifiers
 * X Extra types / values
 * X Missing type / value
 * X Missing identifier
 * X Incorrect identifier
 * - Invalid variable lookup (nonexistant variable) (also applies when setting vars)
 * - Type mismatch when setting variables (interpreter)
 * - Type mismatch during lookups (interpreter)
 * - Attempt to make a new variable with the same name as an existing one (handle this in the interpreter?)
 * X Attempt to use an identifier as a variable identifier
 *
 * General errors:
 * X Missing semicolons
 * - Unexpected tokens outside of statements (i.e. a random character on its own line)
 * X Unfinished string literals
 * X Unfinished block comments
 *:

:: Variable declaration tests
var a : int;
var b : float;
var c : bool;
var d : string;

:: Variable initialization tests
var w, 10;
var x, 5.5;
var y, true;
var z, "test of string literal";

:: Variable setting tests
set a, 15;
set b, 9.87;
set c, false;
set d, "test of set instruction";

:: Error tests (comment out if not testing errors)

:: missing semicolon
::var j : int

:: extra identifier / type / value
::var e f : int;
::var f : int int;
::var g, 10 10;
::set a b, 10;

:: missing type / value
::var h : ;
::var i, ;
::set a, ;

:: missing identifier
::var , 10;
::var : int;
::set , 10;

:: open string literal
::var z2, "test of string literal pt 2;

:: "set" type mismatch (needs implemented with the interpreter)
::set a, 9.87;